				<name type="primary" sortindex="1" value="暗战三国 (Three Kingdoms In The Dark)" />
			
						                           
						               													<description>&amp;#230;&amp;#154;&amp;#151;&amp;#230;&amp;#136;&amp;#152;&amp;#228;&amp;#184;&amp;#137;&amp;#229;&amp;#155;&amp;#189; (&amp;quot;Three Kingdoms In The Dark&amp;quot;) is a card game based on the Chinese classical novel, Romance of the Three Kingdoms. &amp;#10;The object of this game is to find and defeat the group of opponents by talking, voting and using card abilities. It refers to two classic game &amp;lsquo;Legends of The Three Kingdoms&amp;rsquo; and &amp;lsquo;The Werewolves of Miller's Hollow.&amp;rsquo;&amp;#10;     The game flow is similar as Werewovers. The phases are divided into Day and Night. The players close their eyes and wake up separately to use ability in the Night. They start talking in sequence in the Day and using card ability. They vote together after everyone finishes speaking in sequence. &amp;#10;The difference is: &amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Each player can hold 2 characters&amp;rsquo; cards, one character card is primary identity and another one is vice identity. &amp;#10;     Each player has 2 health points in the beginning. &amp;#10;     The player can disclose only one character card in the Day in the whole game and use that ability. &amp;#10;     There are 3 roles in the games: the Ambitiousness, the Royal and the Civilian. There are  two groups. One group is the Ambitiousness, another group is the Royal and the Civilian. There are four kingdoms: WEI, SHU, WU and QUN. &amp;#10;     In the Night, the Ambitiousness launch two night attack which will damage totally 2 health points on one or two players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
